classDiagram
    title Chapter 16: Sized vs Unsized Types
    
    class SizedTypes {
        <<Sized>>
        i32, f64
        String
        Vec~T~
        Structs
        Arrays~N~
    }
    
    class UnsizedTypes {
        <<~Sized>>
        str
        [T]
        dyn Trait
        Slice~T~
    }
    
    class References {
        &str
        &[T]
        Box~dyn Trait~
        Rc~dyn Trait~
    }
    
    SizedTypes --> References : Can be on stack
    UnsizedTypes --> References : Must be behind pointer
    
    Note over SizedTypes: Known size at compile\nStored on stack
    Note over UnsizedTypes: Dynamic size\nMust use &T, Box, Rc
